The paper focuses on the relationship between editorial board members and scientific output in the field of chemistry, which suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as well as cybernetics (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of time-series data and Granger causality test suggests a potential focus on signal processing (cs.SI).
